AN actor, Richard Mofe-Damijo, is among over 25 resource persons to speak at a Pan-African virtual conference tagged ‘Recall for Men conference.’ The conference, which is the third edition, will take place from the May 28 to 30. Designed for men between 20 and 35 years old, the three-day conference has its theme as ‘The future is here’. The Chief Coaching Officer at the Yetunde Bernard Company and convener of the event, Yetunde Bankole-Bernard, in a statement on Monday, said, “This year’s conference seeks to address the challenges and difficulties of the 21st century man in an authentic, truthful, and realistic way to enable him to navigate life with more clarity and make better decisions. “It is targeted at providing the African man living in today’s urban, competitive and demanding society with insights and practical tools to enable him to meet his evolving world with intention, clarity, a deep sense of tenacity and thrive not only in Africa’s peculiar socio-cultural terrain but globally.” She also said this three-day free virtual conference is divided into keynote sessions, panel discussions, global business sessions, and specialised paid master classes. Apart from Mofe-Damijo, expected Pan-African resource persons include Jorge Maciel, Mozambique; Chibamba Kanyama, Zambia; Dr Baba Buntu, South Africa; Pompi, Zambia; The Real Femi, Nigeria; Mi Abaga, Nigeria. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com